The paper deals with modeling networks, which is a common topic in several sub-categories of computer science. However, the focus on latent Euclidean embedding and the introduction of a new model for network analysis suggests that the paper is most likely to belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. The use of an EM algorithm for fitting the model suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Other possible sub-categories include Statistical Learning (cs.SD), Network Analysis and Optimization (cs.NE), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
